casebody.data:
No. 13,

Original.

Wisconsin v. Tennessee. Vernon W. Thomson, Attorney General, Stewart G. Honeck, Deputy Attorney General, and Roy G. Tulane and George F. Sieker, Assistant Attorneys General, for the State of Wisconsin, plaintiff. George F. McCanless, Attorney General, Allison B. Humphreys, Jr., Solicitor General, and Knox Bingham and James M. Glasgow, Assistant Attorneys General, for the State of Tennessee, defendant.

This case is set for hearing during the week of January 23 on the motion for leave to file the complaint.
